"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-01-olympics-2024-womens-football-all-8-countries-that-qualified-for-quarter-final-list\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  All the eight countries that have qualified for the Paris 2024 Olympics women's football event have been confirmed.  The countries are France, Canada, Colombia, United States, Germany, Spain, Brazil and Japan.  This follows the conclusion of Wednesday's group stage fixtures.  Japan defeated Nigeria's Super Falcons 3-1.  Spain also defeated Brazil 2-0 in the other group-stage fixture.  The quarter-final fixtures will commence on Saturday.  Offor grateful for Kano Pillars experience  Preseason: Why Arsenal lost 2-1 to Liverpool - Arteta  Olympics 2024: I borrowed bicycle from Germans to compete - Nigerian cyclist, Ukpeseraye  Olympics 2024: 'Great rivalry has been created' - Lacazette on France beating Argentina  Olympics 2024: Sports Minister updates on Favour Ofili's 100m race exclusion, raises posers  Olympics 2024: Rosemary Chukwuma qualifies for women's 100m semifinals  Olympics 2024: Mixed reactions from Nigerians as Super Falcons crash out  Olympics 2024: Stop bad-mouthing Super Falcons - Ayinde rallies support for teammates  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"